{
  "text": "Lattice system In the vdW-DF method, we work with a local-field susceptibility \u03b1 and corresponding external-field susceptibility \u03b1 ext = \u03b1/(1 + 4\u03c0\u03b1). This susceptibility (or plasmon propagator) depends on two spatial coordinates but can be represented in a gradient expansion. When investigating the asymptotic interactions, the relevant limit is [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] :",
